<item>
            <title>[LU-833] Readonly patch way too verbose</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-833</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running replay-single.sh/replay-ost-single.sh, the console logs is &lt;b&gt;flooded&lt;/b&gt; with messages like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Release to readonly device dm-0 (0xfd00000): [inode 18] [block 39994] [count 5] [is_meta 1]
Lustre: Failing over lustre-OST0000
Write to readonly device dm-0 (0xfd00000) bi_flags: f000000000000001, bi_vcnt: 1, bi_idx: 0, bi-&amp;gt;size: 4096, bi_cnt: 2, bi_private: ffff8800750ddf00
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although i understand the need of printing debug information to the console, it makes it really difficult to find useful information in the middle of all this noise.&lt;br/&gt;
e.g. for &lt;b&gt;just&lt;/b&gt; replay-ost-single/test 8:&lt;br/&gt;
$ grep &quot;Write to readonly&quot; replay-ost-single.test_8.console.client-25vm8.log | wc -l&lt;br/&gt;
538&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This additional debug information was added in bugzilla 16680:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;commit 2d3aaef4122c11dcb6d892da89522ffa37036136
Author: Fan Yong &amp;lt;Yong.Fan@Sun.COM&amp;gt;
Date:   Thu Feb 25 00:32:12 2010 -0800

    b=16680 diagnostic patch to verify lustre read-only device mechanism
    
    Diagnostic patch to check whether lustre read-only device mechanism works well or not.
    
    i=alex.zhuravlev
    i=rahul.deshmukh
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we are now confident that the read-only patch works well now, i would like to disable those debug information. If not, it probably deserves more digging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
